    "narrative": "Ghost Ride the WHIP enters April 25th with **Corbin Carroll** standing as our undisputed anchor. With a commanding score of 85.93, **Corbin Carroll** benefits from a massive 19% SP skill boost against M\u00e1rquez and, crucially, a 4% efficiency bump due to a favorable matchup for stolen base upside\u2014a priority given our league's scarcity. Joining him in the top tier are **Seiya Suzuki** and **Brice Turang**, who capitalize on high-order positioning and soft matchups against Roki Sasaki and Mitch Keller, respectively. **Brice Turang** in particular sees his value inflated to 66.72 by his assumed leadoff spot and a 10% order bonus, keeping him as a vital engine for our run production today.\n\nThe most difficult decision on the bench centered on **Alex Freeland**, who posted a respectable 49.73 score but ultimately lost his spot to our more established starters. **Alex Freeland** was squeezed out largely by his projected #9 spot in the order, which carried a -8% penalty that neutralized his switch-hitting upside and the wind assistance. While **Austin Riley** remains a constant talent, he faces an uphill battle against the elite command of Zack Wheeler, suppressing his score well below our starting threshold. We continue to monitor the status of **Mickey Moniak**, whose game has already been flagged as a rainout, ensuring he stays firmly on the bench to preserve our limited game caps. \n\nRisk management remains paramount today, particularly with several lineups still marked as \"Pending.\" While **Dalton Rushing**, **Jazz Chisholm Jr.**, **Max Muncy**, **Giancarlo Stanton**, **Tyler Soderstrom**, and **Vinnie Pasquantino** all carry solid projections, their efficiency ratings are heavily dependent on confirmed placement in the batting order. We are closely tracking **Vinnie Pasquantino**, who faces a very tough outing against Walbert Urena; despite his 14% platoon edge, his output is capped by Urena\u2019s elite skill level. We are confident in this configuration, trusting that the speed profile of our outfield\u2014anchored by **Corbin Carroll** and **James Wood**\u2014will provide the necessary buffer in our most scarce category.",
